cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SY. 

This paper deals with the formal modelling of container-based systems, which are commonly used in cloud-based architectures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of formal methods to reason about properties of container systems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). The use of graph theory and bigraphical reactive systems also suggests that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper deals with the composition of containers, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
